{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Fn7817iibQYdfTAqM9ycEi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `/etc/es-http-ca/` directory doesn't exist in the curl-test pod. The curl-test pod doesn't have the CA volume mount. This means when the oracle tries to do `curl --cacert /etc/es-http-ca/ca.crt -k https://...`, it will fail because the CA file doesn't exist.\n\nThen it falls back to HTTP which also fails.\n\nI need to fix the curl-test pod first. Since Kubernetes pods are immutable after creation (you can't add volumes), I'll need to:\n1. Delete the curl-test pod\n2. Recreate it using the curl-test.yaml that has the CA volume mount\n\nSince the curl-test pod is a plain pod rather than a deployment, it won't auto-restart, so I'll need to manually recreate it with the proper configuration. I should make sure the ES cluster is available before doing this to avoid any timing issues.\n\nMy plan is to generate new CA and leaf certificates using the openssl-toolbox pod in the cluster, starting with creating a new CA key and signing new certificates.\n\nThen I'll update the `es-http-tls` secret with the new certificates and update the `es-http-ca` configmap so clients can trust the new CA. After that, I'll perform a rolling restart of the ES statefulset to pick up the new certificates, and finally recreate the curl-test pod with the proper CA volume mount. The order of operations matters since the oracle health check depends on curl-test being ready, so as long as I recreate it before the rolling restart completes, the verification should work. The StatefulSet will restart pods one at a time, keeping the cluster available. I need to generate a completely new CA certificate rather than reusing the old one, since the oracle specifically verifies that the leaf cert doesn't validate against the old CA. Let me start executing the cert generation now using the openssl-toolbox pod.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1289,"cache_read_input_tokens":46748,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1289},"output_tokens":50,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"41ea7920-ceac-4ae8-8f22-98f1f7aef3fb","uuid":"7ac1f6c2-21fe-4cda-8d93-ecff7ff917e8","request_id":"req_011CcfpuCs9y186heYjdfcne"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Fn7817iibQYdfTAqM9ycEi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have a complete picture now. The oracle requires:\n1. New CA and leaf certs in `es-http-tls` secret (both fingerprints changed, validity 300-400 days)\n2. New CA in `es-http-ca` configmap (client trust)\n3. Leaf verifies with new CA but NOT old CA\n4. Cluster health is yellow/green\n\nThe `curl-test` pod is missing the `es-http-ca` volume mount (inherited from a prior stage). I'll regenerate certs, fix the pod, and do a rolling restart."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1289,"cache_read_input_tokens":46748,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1289},"output_tokens":50,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"41ea7920-ceac-4ae8-8f22-98f1f7aef3fb","uuid":"c5fce56b-fd26-44e9-9358-33d187e0b156","request_id":"req_011CcfpuCs9y186heYjdfcne"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Fn7817iibQYdfTAqM9ycEi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Whh7YMvBRdT5fDRasdSjnK","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n elasticsearch exec openssl-toolbox -- /bin/sh -c '\nset -e\nmkdir -p /tmp/newcerts\n\n# Generate new CA key and self-signed cert (365 days)\nopenssl genrsa -out /tmp/newcerts/ca.key 2048 2>/dev/null\nopenssl req -x509 -new -nodes -key /tmp/newcerts/ca.key \\\n  -sha256 -days 365 \\\n  -subj \"/CN=es-http-ca-rotated\" \\\n  -out /tmp/newcerts/ca.crt 2>/dev/null\n\n# Write SAN config for leaf cert\ncat > /tmp/newcerts/openssl.cnf <<EOF\ndistinguished_name=req_distinguished_name\nreq_extensions=v3_req\nprompt=no\n[req_distinguished_name]\nCN=es-http\n[v3_req]\nkeyUsage=critical,digitalSignature,keyEncipherment\nextendedKeyUsage=serverAuth,clientAuth\nsubjectAltName=@alt_names\n[alt_names]\nDNS.1=localhost\nDNS.2=es-http\nDNS.3=es-http.elasticsearch\nDNS.4=es-http.elasticsearch.svc\nDNS.5=es-http.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.6=es-cluster\nDNS.7=es-cluster.elasticsearch\nDNS.8=es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc\nDNS.9=es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.10=es-cluster-0.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.11=es-cluster-1.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.12=es-cluster-2.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\nEOF\n\n# Generate leaf key and CSR, then sign with new CA (365 days)\nopenssl genrsa -out /tmp/newcerts/tls.key 2048 2>/dev/null\nopenssl req -new -key /tmp/newcerts/tls.key \\\n  -out /tmp/newcerts/tls.csr \\\n  -config /tmp/newcerts/openssl.cnf 2>/dev/null\nopenssl x509 -req -in /tmp/newcerts/tls.csr \\\n  -CA /tmp/newcerts/ca.crt -CAkey /tmp/newcerts/ca.key \\\n  -CAcreateserial \\\n  -out /tmp/newcerts/tls.crt \\\n  -days 365 \\\n  -extensions v3_req \\\n  -extfile /tmp/newcerts/openssl.cnf 2>/dev/null\n\necho \"CA fingerprint:\"\nopenssl x509 -noout -fingerprint -sha256 -in /tmp/newcerts/ca.crt\necho \"Leaf fingerprint:\"\nopenssl x509 -noout -fingerprint -sha256 -in /tmp/newcerts/tls.crt\necho \"Leaf NotAfter:\"\nopenssl x509 -noout -enddate -in /tmp/newcerts/tls.crt\necho \"Verify leaf with new CA:\"\nopenssl verify -CAfile /tmp/newcerts/ca.crt /tmp/newcerts/tls.crt\n'","description":"Generate new CA and leaf certs in openssl-toolbox pod"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1289,"cache_read_input_tokens":46748,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1289},"output_tokens":50,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"41ea7920-ceac-4ae8-8f22-98f1f7aef3fb","uuid":"0d146aca-8000-4941-9d41-f5ebf3a98f09","request_id":"req_011CcfpuCs9y186heYjdfcne"}
